  "time_ut": 1661747449,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0dc0\u0dd2\u0daf\u0dd4\u0dbd\u0dd2\u0db6\u0dbd \u0d87\u0db8\u0dad\u0dd2\u0d9c\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca \u0dc0\u0dd2\u0db4\u0d9a\u0dca\u0dc2\u0dba\u0da7 \u0dba\u0ddd\u0da2\u0db1\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0d9a\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "A proposal from the power minister to the opposition",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Mr. Kanchana Wijesekera, Minister of Electricity and Energy, said that the opposition will be asked to appoint a parliamentary committee on the procurement of fuel and coal and accept the position of its chairman.",
        "Mr. Champika Ranawaka and several MPs have said that fuel can be sold at a low price. The minister said that he would be happy as the minister in charge if such a committee was formed and handed over to the opposition."
      ],
